{
  "texts": [
    "The thin blue line is the ground-state energy, the thick orange line represents the band of excited states (see the inset for a zoom into that region).",
    "For any finite J/t0, the band of excited states is separated from the ground state by an excitation gap of O(J).",
    "By calculating the spectral-weighted average of the local spin-spin operator from Eq.",
    "(A1), we observe that the ground state is a singlet [K c,f (Ψgs)] and the excited states are in the triplet sector [K c,f (Ψex)] for large J/t0, as expected [32].that, for large J/t 0, these approach:K cf (Ψ gs) = - 3 4 + t 2 0 J 2 (A2)andK cf (Ψ ex) = 1 4 + 1 L t 2 0 J 2, (A3)respectively.",
    "Moreover, the following dependence of S cf on J/t 0 emerges in this limit in the steady state:S cf (t → ∞) = P gs K c,f (Ψ gs) + P ex K c,f (Ψ ex) = - 1 4 + 2 + 1 2L t 2 0 J 2 + O(J -4)."
  ]
